          <li><strong>4x4s training:</strong> Climb 4 routes at your onsight grade (e.g., 5.10b) back-to-back with minimal rest. Repeat 4 times. This builds pump resistance</li>
          <li><strong>Projecting technique:</strong> Spend 70% of time onsighting/flashing, 30% projecting harder routes. Break projects into sections and link them</li>
          <li><strong>Footwork refinement:</strong> Silent feet drills, precise placements, flagging - technique still trumps power</li>
          <li><strong>Key milestone:</strong> When you can consistently redpoint 5.11c and flash 5.11a, you're approaching advanced level</li>
